        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "CLI: clarify gateway url override auth hints",
        "body": "## Summary\r\n- improve the gateway URL override auth error with source-specific follow-up hints\r\n- tell CLI users they can remove `--url` when they meant the default local or SSH-tunneled gateway\r\n- tell env override users to set `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_TOKEN` or `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_PASSWORD` alongside `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_URL`\r\n\r\n## Why\r\nOpenClaw already correctly rejects gateway URL overrides unless explicit credentials are provided, but the current error is still easy to stumble over in real Docker, VPS, and TUI flows.\r\n\r\nThis update keeps the same security behavior while making the failure more actionable:\r\n- CLI `--url` users get a hint that they may not need `--url` at all for the default local or tunneled gateway\r\n- `OPENCLAW_GATEWAY_URL` users get a direct explanation that env URL overrides do not reuse config-only credentials and must be paired with explicit env auth\r\n\r\nThat makes the secure path easier to understand without loosening the override guard.\r\n\r\n## Testing\r\n- [x] `pnpm test -- src/gateway/call.test.ts`\r\n- [x] `pnpm test -- src/tui/gateway-chat.test.ts`\r\n- [x] `pnpm build`\r\n\r\n## AI assistance\r\nAI-assisted. I verified the final code change, reviewed the surrounding call paths, and ran the targeted tests and build locally.",
